 chapters, each devoted to a different color, they examine the various ways colors have shaped and continue to shape our social and moral imaginations. Each individual color becomes the focal point for a consideration of one of the extraordinary ways in which color appears and matters in our lives. Beautifully produced in full color, this book is a remarkably smart, entertaining, and fascinating guide to this elusive topic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aColorsxHistory. 0aColorsxSocial aspects. 0aColors. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh1 aFarthing , Stephen, eauthor.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235425.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles